# Modern CSS And Nesting

- Prefer modern CSS features with progressive enhancement and practical fallbacks.
- Use native CSS nesting for component styles (`&__element`, `&--modifier`, `&.state`) instead of flat repeated selectors.
- Keep styles component-scoped and colocated; avoid broad global selectors for component internals.
- Use CSS custom properties for tunable values and animation/layout handoff from JS.
- For new focus/overlay UI, prefer layout systems (`grid`/`flex`) over manual fixed positioning unless behavior requires it.
